---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Nav from '../../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../../components/Breadcrumb.astro';
import CTABlock from '../../components/CTABlock.astro';
import ServiceCard from '../../components/ServiceCard.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About | Untitled Mixed Media | Hand-Painted Murals and Signs in Richmond, VA"
  description="We don't start with a sketch. We start with research. Hand-painted murals and signs in Richmond, Virginia. Fully insured. No templates. No signature style."
>
  <Nav />
  <main class="pt-24 pb-16">
    <div class="px-6 lg:px-12 max-w-7xl mx-auto">
      <Breadcrumb items={[
        { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
        { label: 'About' },
      ]} />

      <!-- Hero: split layout -->
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-12 gap-8 lg:gap-16 mb-20">
        <div class="lg:col-span-7">
          <p class="font-mono text-smoke-gray uppercase mb-4" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-xs); letter-spacing: var(--tracking-wider);">
            About
          </p>
          <h1 class="font-heading text-titanium-white mb-6 text-balance" data-animate="headline" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-4xl); line-height: 1.05;">
            Most artists want everyone to know their name. We want everyone to know yours.
          </h1>
        </div>
        <div class="lg:col-span-5 lg:flex lg:items-end">
          <p class="font-body text-shadow-gray" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);" data-animate>
            Your building is doing the talking whether you want it to or not. Right now it's saying the same thing as every other storefront on the block: nothing. You've put real work into your business. The product is right. The team is solid. But people drive past every day without slowing down. The outside doesn't match what's inside.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Pull quote — full width -->
      <div class="text-center py-12 mb-20" data-animate="settle">
        <p class="font-heading text-titanium-white italic max-w-3xl mx-auto" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-2xl); line-height: var(--leading-snug);">
          We don't start with a sketch. We start with research.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Two-column editorial body -->
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 lg:gap-20 mb-20">
        <div class="space-y-6" data-animate="fade" data-animate-delay="1">
          <p class="font-body text-shadow-gray" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-lg); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);">
            Most muralists show up with a portfolio and ask what you want on your wall. I show up with questions.
          </p>
          <p class="font-body text-shadow-gray" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);">
            What's the story behind this building? What does the neighborhood look like at 7 AM versus 7 PM? What do your customers notice when they walk up? What do they miss? I spend time in the space before I ever think about a design. I study the materials, the architecture, the light, the history. The answers are already in the building. My job is to find them and paint them.
          </p>
          <p class="font-body text-titanium-white" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);">
            When the design comes from what's already there, the result is different. The mural doesn't look like it was applied to the building. It looks like it was always part of it.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-6" data-animate="fade" data-animate-delay="2">
          <p class="font-body text-shadow-gray" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);">
            The name says it. "Untitled" because every project starts blank. No templates loaded. No predetermined style to impose. We don't have a signature look, and that's the point. The work should look like it belongs to your building, not to us. "Mixed media" because the question is never "what medium do we work in." The question is "what does this specific place, this specific story, this specific moment need?" Whatever that answer requires, that's what we use.
          </p>
          <p class="font-body text-shadow-gray" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);">
            I'm Spencer Bennett. I run Untitled Mixed Media out of Richmond, Virginia. I paint murals and signs for businesses, property owners, and public institutions. Mineral paints, gold leaf, commercial-grade enamels. Materials that weather into a building's character instead of peeling off it. Fully insured. Licensed in Virginia. Experienced in historic districts.
          </p>
          <p class="font-body text-shadow-gray" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);">
            If you have a wall, a building, or even just an idea you haven't figured out yet, that's enough. I'll help you build it into something worth painting.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Sub-pages: asymmetric grid -->
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <div class="lg:col-span-2" data-animate="fade" data-animate-delay="1">
          <ServiceCard
            title="Process"
            description="How we discover the story your building already holds."
            href="/about/process"
          />
        </div>
        <div data-animate="fade" data-animate-delay="2">
          <ServiceCard
            title="Philosophy"
            description="Why we start with discovery, not design."
            href="/about/philosophy"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8 mt-8">
        <div data-animate="fade" data-animate-delay="3">
          <ServiceCard
            title="Insurance & Licensing"
            description="Credentials, coverage, and compliance."
            href="/about/insurance-and-licensing"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <CTABlock />

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
